---
title: Lean Cajun Turkey Steak with Crushed Beans and Chipotle-Spiced Slaw
description: Super lean and packed with protein, turkey is a great addition to this weeknight favourite and works brilliantly with the punchy cajun spices it is coated in. Served with a crunchy chipotle spiced slaw and creamy crushed beans, this healthy recipe is the perfect thing for an easy mid-week dinner. Top with chopped coriander, spring onion, a squeeze of fresh lime, and dig in!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/cajun-turkey-steak-6b96307e-7e79dfea.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipecards/card/cajun-turkey-steak-5c40b0d8c445fa73e256d991-67739a32.pdf
servings: 2
nutrition:
  calories: 402 kcal
  fat: 8 g
  saturated fat: 3 g
  carbohydrates: 28 g
  sugar: 13 g
  protein: 52 g
  sodium: 1 g
  serving size: 476
time required: 20 minutes
source: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipes/cajun-turkey-steak-5c40b0d8c445fa73e256d991
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
cuisine: Fusion
---

Halve, peel and chop the @red onion{1}(peeled and chopped) into small pieces.

Zest, then halve the @lime{1}.

Roughly chop the @fresh coriander{1}(roughly chopped) (stalks and all).

Drain and rinse the @mixed beans{1%400g can} in a #sieve{}.

Heat a splash of @oil{} in a #saucepan{} over medium heat.

When hot, add the onion. Stir and cook until soft, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Sprinkle on half the @Central American Style Spice Mix{1/2} then stir and cook
until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the beans.

Add the @water{100%ml} and stir in the @chicken stock powder{1/2}.

Bring to the boil, lower then heat, then use a #potato masher{} to mash the
beans as they cook.

Lower the heat and simmer until most of the water has evaporated and the
beans have a hummus consistency, ~{6-7%minutes}. Stir frequently.

Meanwhile, heat a splash of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} over medium-high
heat.

Season the @British turkey steaks{2} with @salt{} and sprinkle on the remaining
Cajun spice blend.

When the oil is hot, add the turkey steaks and brown for ~{2%minutes} on each
side. Lower the heat to medium and cook until the turkey is no longer pink in
the middle, another ~{3-4%minutes} on each side.

> IMPORTANT: The turkey is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Use a coarse #grater{} to grate the @apple{1}(grated) (no need to peel) into a
#mixing bowl{} then pop in the @coleslaw mix{120%g}.

Stir in the @Greek style natural yoghurt{75%g}, @chipotle paste{10%g} and half
the lime zest.

Season with @salt{} and lime juice to taste. Stir in half the coriander.

When the beans are ready, stir in the remaining lime zest and share between your
plates. Pop the slaw alongside.

Slice the turkey thinly and arrange on top of the beans and finish with a
sprinkle of remaining coriander and a final squeeze of lime.